# Store Locator — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the values for your workspace.
#
# These variables are managed by the AIO CLI (`aio app use`) and are
# automatically populated when you select a workspace. You generally
# do not need to set them manually.

## Adobe I/O Runtime credentials (auto-populated by `aio app use`)
# AIO_runtime_namespace=
# AIO_runtime_auth=

## Optional: override the log level for Runtime actions (default: debug)
# LOG_LEVEL=debug

## Commerce API Configuration
# 
# NOTE: With App Management (app.commerce.config.js), credentials are now
# configured via Commerce Admin (Apps > App Management) instead of env vars.
# The inventory-proxy action retrieves credentials securely at runtime.
#
# Required for PaaS/On-Premise (OAuth 1.0a):
# - Set up an Integration in Commerce Admin (System > Extensions > Integrations)
# - Configure credentials in App Management UI
#
# Required for SaaS (IMS):
# - Ensure IMS is configured for your organization
# - Configure credentials in App Management UI
#
# Legacy variables (still used if not using App Management):
# COMMERCE_BASE_URL=https://your-commerce-instance.com
# COMMERCE_CONSUMER_KEY=your-consumer-key
# COMMERCE_CONSUMER_SECRET=your-consumer-secret
# COMMERCE_ACCESS_TOKEN=your-access-token
# COMMERCE_ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET=your-access-token-secret
